00:43:10,968 --> 00:43:12,629
<i>Oh, I'm sorry, excuse me.</i>

452
00:43:12,737 --> 00:43:15,399
<i>- Mrs. Lovett, sir.
- A pleasure, ma'am.</i>

453
00:43:16,273 --> 00:43:18,332
<i>Mr. Todd,
there's a girl who needs my help.</i>

454
00:43:18,442 --> 00:43:20,467
<i>Such a sad girl and lonely,
but beautiful, too and...</i>

455
00:43:20,578 --> 00:43:24,139
<i>- Slow down, son.
- Yes. I'm sorry.</i>

456
00:43:25,583 --> 00:43:27,517
<i>This girl has a guardian
who keeps her locked away,</i>

457
00:43:27,618 --> 00:43:29,677
<i>but then, this morning,
she dropped this.</i>

458
00:43:29,787 --> 00:43:32,051
Surely a sign
that Johanna wants me to help her.

459
00:43:32,156 --> 00:43:33,714
<i>That's her name, Johanna.</i>

460
00:43:33,824 --> 00:43:37,055
And Turpin is her guardian.
He's a judge of some sort.

461
00:43:37,161 --> 00:43:39,095
<i>Once he goes to court,
I'm going to slip into the house,</i>

462
00:43:39,196 --> 00:43:41,562
release her and beg her
to come away with me tonight.

463
00:43:41,666 --> 00:43:44,066
<i>- Oh, this is very romantic.
- Yes.</i>

464
00:43:45,102 --> 00:43:47,161
<i>But I don't know anyone in London,
you see.</i>

465
00:43:47,271 --> 00:43:51,264
And I need somewhere safe to bring her
till I've hired a coach to take us away.

466
00:43:51,375 --> 00:43:53,400
<i>If I could keep her here
just for an hour or two,</i>

467
00:43:53,511 --> 00:43:55,741
I'd be forever in your debt.

468
00:43:59,517 --> 00:44:02,953
<i>- Bring her here, love.
- Thank you, ma'am.</i>

469
00:44:03,921 --> 00:44:05,286
Mr. Todd?

470
00:44:07,191 --> 00:44:09,386
<i>Oh, thank you.
Thank you, thank you, my friend.</i>

471
00:44:09,493 --> 00:44:11,188
<i>Thank you, ma'am.</i>

472
00:44:14,298 --> 00:44:17,790
<i>Seems like the Fates
are favoring you at last, Mr. T.</i>

473
00:44:19,236 --> 00:44:22,728
What is it? You'll have her back
before the day is out.

474
00:44:23,507 --> 00:44:24,804
What about him?

475
00:44:25,776 --> 00:44:26,936
Him?

476
00:44:27,044 --> 00:44:29,638
<i>Oh, well. Let him bring her here.</i>

477
00:44:29,747 --> 00:44:32,648
<i>And then, since you're so hot for a little,</i>

478
00:44:33,884 --> 00:44:36,409
<i>that's the throat to slit, my dear.</i>

479
00:44:38,189 --> 00:44:39,952
Poor little Johanna.

480
00:44:40,057 --> 00:44:43,493
All those years without a scrap
of motherly affection.

481
00:44:43,994 --> 00:44:47,088
<i>Well, I'll soon see to that.</i>

482
00:44:55,306 --> 00:44:58,605
Hello. What's he doing here?

483
00:45:00,611 --> 00:45:02,875
Keep the boy downstairs.

484
00:45:14,191 --> 00:45:16,625
<i>Signora, is Mr. Todd at home?</i>

485
00:45:16,727 --> 00:45:18,854
Plying his trade upstairs.

486
00:45:19,930 --> 00:45:21,591
Would you look at it now?

487
00:45:21,699 --> 00:45:24,190
<i>You wouldn't mind if I gave it a nice
juicy meat pie, would you?</i>

488
00:45:24,301 --> 00:45:28,101
<i>- Sì, sì, sì. Whatever you want.
- Come on, lad.</i>

489
00:45:28,572 --> 00:45:30,972
<i>Your teeth are strong, I hope.</i>

490
00:45:32,510 --> 00:45:36,071
Close the door.
Get you a nice lovely pie.

491
00:45:38,916 --> 00:45:41,248
Sit down. Make yourself comfy.

492
00:45:48,726 --> 00:45:50,159
Come in.

493
00:45:59,036 --> 00:46:01,732
- Mr. Todd.
- Signor Pirelli.

494
00:46:03,340 --> 00:46:04,830
Call me Davey.

495
00:46:05,876 --> 00:46:09,243
Davey Collin's the name
when it's not professional.

496
00:46:10,481 --> 00:46:12,915
<i>I'd like me five quid back,
if you don't mind.</i>

497
00:46:13,017 --> 00:46:14,109
Why?

498
00:46:14,218 --> 00:46:18,245
<i>Because you entered into our little
wager under false pretenses, my friend.</i>

499
00:46:18,355 --> 00:46:22,985
<i>So that you might remember
to be a bit more forthright in the future,</i>

500
00:46:23,093 --> 00:46:25,027
I'll be taking half your profits
from herewith.

501
00:46:25,129 --> 00:46:27,063
Share and share alike.

502
00:46:28,599 --> 00:46:30,999
Mr. Benjamin Barker.

503
00:46:33,537 --> 00:46:36,597
Here we are. Tuck in.

504
00:46:40,211 --> 00:46:43,146
I like to see a man
with a healthy appetite.

505
00:46:43,247 --> 00:46:45,545
Reminds me of my dear Albert.

506
00:46:46,150 --> 00:46:49,745
<i>Liked to gorge himself
to bloatation, he did.</i>

507
00:46:49,854 --> 00:46:52,152
<i>He didn't have
your nice head of hair, though.</i>

508
00:46:52,256 --> 00:46:55,487
<i>To tell the truth, it gets awful hot.</i>

509
00:46:59,663 --> 00:47:01,824
<i>Yes, this'll do nicely.</i>

510
00:47:05,469 --> 00:47:08,802
<i>You don't remember me, do you?
Why should you?</i>

511
00:47:08,906 --> 00:47:11,238
<i>I was just a little nip
that you hired for a couple of weeks,</i>

512
00:47:11,342 --> 00:47:13,310
sweeping up hair.

513
00:47:14,245 --> 00:47:16,304
But I remember these.

514
00:47:17,147 --> 00:47:20,173
<i>And how could
I ever forget you, Mr. Barker.</i>

515
00:47:24,488 --> 00:47:26,649
I used to sit right here.

516
00:47:27,591 --> 00:47:30,458
Dream of the day
when I could be a proper barber myself.

517
00:47:30,561 --> 00:47:34,292
You might say that you was
inspiration to me.

518
00:47:46,644 --> 00:47:48,509
<i>So, is we got a deal?</i>

519
00:47:49,914 --> 00:47:53,941
<i>Or should I run down the street
to me old pal, Beadle Bamford?</i>

520
00:47:57,554 --> 00:48:01,752
<i>What do you say to that, now,
Mr. Sweeney Todd?</i>

521
00:48:24,415 --> 00:48:27,441
<i>My, my, my. Always work to be done.</i>

522
00:48:27,551 --> 00:48:29,883
<i>Spic and span, that's my motto.</i>

523
00:48:42,566 --> 00:48:45,933
<i>So, how'd you end up
with that dreadful Italian?</i>

524
00:48:46,036 --> 00:48:50,405
Got me from the workhouse.
Been there since I was born.

525
00:48:50,507 --> 00:48:53,101
<i>Oh, God!
He's got an appointment with his tailor!</i>

526
00:48:53,210 --> 00:48:54,802
<i>If he's late, he'll blame me!</i>

527
00:48:54,912 --> 00:48:56,174
Wait!

528
00:49:02,820 --> 00:49:05,345
Signor! You got an appointment!

529
00:49:10,594 --> 00:49:14,394
Signor Pirelli's been called away.
Better run after him.

530
00:49:15,366 --> 00:49:19,803
<i>No, sir. I should stay here,
or it'll be a lashing.</i>

531
00:49:19,903 --> 00:49:22,599
He's a great one for the lashings.

532
00:49:28,479 --> 00:49:29,639
<i>So,</i>

533
00:49:30,948 --> 00:49:34,884
<i>- Mrs. Lovett gave you a pie, did she?
- She's a real lady.</i>

534
00:49:35,753 --> 00:49:37,380
That she is.

535
00:49:42,259 --> 00:49:47,253
<i>But if I know a growing boy,
there's still room for more pie, eh?</i>

536
00:49:47,364 --> 00:49:48,661
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

537
00:49:49,933 --> 00:49:52,731
Then why don't you wait
for your master downstairs?

538
00:49:52,836 --> 00:49:57,205
<i>- Be another pie in it for you, I'm sure.
- No, I should stay here.</i>

539
00:49:59,943 --> 00:50:03,879
<i>Tell you what,
why don't you tell Mrs. Lovett</i>

540
00:50:03,981 --> 00:50:07,439
that I said to give you
a nice big tot of gin.

541
00:50:07,551 --> 00:50:09,109
<i>Thank you, sir!</i>

542
00:51:17,121 --> 00:51:19,419
<i>This is the second time, sir,</i>

543
00:51:19,523 --> 00:51:22,651
you have been brought
before this bench.

544
00:51:23,894 --> 00:51:27,990
<i>Though it is my earnest wish ever
to temper justice with mercy,</i>

545
00:51:28,098 --> 00:51:31,261
your persistent dedication
to a life of crime

546
00:51:31,368 --> 00:51:35,031
is an abomination before God and man.

547
00:51:35,139 --> 00:51:38,597
I therefore sentence you
to hang by the neck until you're dead.

548
00:51:38,709 --> 00:51:41,678
And may the Lord
have mercy on your soul.

549
00:51:42,746 --> 00:51:44,509
Court is adjourned.

550
00:51:53,490 --> 00:51:55,981
<i>Thank you, Your Honor.</i>

551
00:51:56,093 --> 00:51:59,529
- Just the sentence we wanted.
- Was he guilty?

552
00:51:59,630 --> 00:52:00,756
<i>Well, if he didn't do it,</i>

553
00:52:00,864 --> 00:52:03,298
he's surely done
something to warrant a hanging.

554
00:52:03,400 --> 00:52:06,096
- What man has not?
- Sorry?

555
00:52:09,106 --> 00:52:10,869
No matter. Come.

556
00:52:12,075 --> 00:52:13,736
Walk home with me.

557
00:52:16,780 --> 00:52:19,476
<i>I have news for you, my friend.</i>

558
00:52:19,583 --> 00:52:22,609
<i>In order to shield her
from the evils of this world,</i>

559
00:52:22,719 --> 00:52:26,052
I have decided to marry
my dear Johanna.

560
00:52:26,156 --> 00:52:28,556
<i>Sir, happy news indeed.</i>

561
00:52:28,659 --> 00:52:30,217
<i>Strange though,</i>

562
00:52:30,827 --> 00:52:36,493
<i>when I offered myself to her,
she showed a certain reluctance.</i>

563
00:52:37,401 --> 00:52:40,097
<i>Excuse me, my lord
May I request, my lord</i>

564
00:52:40,204 --> 00:52:42,604
<i>Permission, my lord, to speak?</i>

565
00:52:42,706 --> 00:52:44,970
<i>Forgive me if I suggest, my lord</i>

566
00:52:45,075 --> 00:52:47,441
<i>You're looking less
than your best, my lord</i>

567
00:52:47,544 --> 00:52:52,243
<i>There's powder upon your vest, my lord
And stubble upon your cheek</i>

568
00:52:55,385 --> 00:52:59,287
<i>And ladies, my lord, are weak</i>

569
00:53:00,090 --> 00:53:02,354
<i>Stubble, you say?</i>

570
00:53:05,696 --> 00:53:09,154
Perhaps I am
a little overhasty in the mornings.

571
00:53:10,267 --> 00:53:12,735
<i>Fret not though, my lord
I know a place, my lord</i>

572
00:53:12,836 --> 00:53:15,361
<i>A barber, my lord, of skill</i>

573
00:53:15,472 --> 00:53:17,667
<i>Thus armed with a shaven face, my lord</i>

574
00:53:17,774 --> 00:53:20,072
<i>Some eau de cologne to grace, my lord</i>

575
00:53:20,177 --> 00:53:22,645
<i>And musk to enhance the chase
my lord</i>

576
00:53:22,746 --> 00:53:25,613
<i>You'll dazzle the girl until</i>

577
00:53:26,516 --> 00:53:27,881
Until?

578
00:53:28,452 --> 00:53:32,650
<i>She bows to your every will</i>

579
00:53:33,724 --> 00:53:35,021
Barber?

580
00:53:36,326 --> 00:53:37,350
Take me to him.

581
00:53:37,461 --> 00:53:42,160
<i>His name is Todd, my lord, and he is
the very last word in barbering.</i>

582
00:53:48,839 --> 00:53:52,275
<i>You ought to slow down a bit, lad.
It'll go straight to your head.</i>

583
00:53:52,376 --> 00:53:53,968
They used to give it to us
in the workhouse

584
00:53:54,077 --> 00:53:55,840
so as we could sleep.

585
00:53:55,946 --> 00:53:58,107
<i>Not that you'd want
to sleep in that place, ma'am.</i>

586
00:53:58,215 --> 00:54:00,581
Not with the things
what happen in the dark.

587
00:54:00,684 --> 00:54:02,015
<i>That's nice, dear.</i>

588
00:54:02,119 --> 00:54:03,950
Think I'll just pop in
on Mr. Todd for a tick.

589
00:54:04,054 --> 00:54:06,887
<i>- You all right, there?
- Leave the bottle.</i>

590
00:54:11,895 --> 00:54:15,296
That lad is drinking me
out of house and home.

591
00:54:16,300 --> 00:54:18,632
How long till Pirelli gets back?

592
00:54:19,269 --> 00:54:20,998
He won't be back.

593
00:54:22,873 --> 00:54:24,738
<i>Mr. T, you didn't.</i>

594
00:54:35,952 --> 00:54:39,547
You're barking mad.
Killing a man what done you no harm.

595
00:54:40,390 --> 00:54:44,326
He recognized me from the old days.
Tried to blackmail me.

596
00:54:45,595 --> 00:54:47,222
Half me earnings.

597
00:54:47,931 --> 00:54:50,729
<i>Oh, well, it's a different matter then.</i>

598
00:54:51,635 --> 00:54:55,127
<i>For a moment there,
I thought you'd lost your marbles.</i>

599
00:54:58,208 --> 00:54:59,835
All that blood.

600
00:55:01,345 --> 00:55:02,812
Poor bugger.

601
00:55:03,680 --> 00:55:05,045
<i>Oh, well.</i>

602
00:55:13,457 --> 00:55:15,857
<i>Well, waste not, want not.</i>

603
00:55:17,494 --> 00:55:20,759
<i>So, what are we gonna do
about the boy then?</i>

604
00:55:22,265 --> 00:55:23,789
Send him up.

605
00:55:24,735 --> 00:55:27,704
<i>Oh, we don't need to worry about him.
He's a simple thing.</i>

606
00:55:27,804 --> 00:55:29,328
Send him up!

607
00:55:32,242 --> 00:55:35,700
<i>Now, Mr. T,
surely one's enough for today.</i>

608
00:55:36,847 --> 00:55:40,339
<i>Besides, I was thinking of hiring the lad
to help me run the shop.</i>

609
00:55:40,450 --> 00:55:43,419
Your poor knees
aren't what they used to be.

610
00:55:44,221 --> 00:55:45,654
All right.

611
00:55:47,691 --> 00:55:49,989
<i>Course, we're gonna
have to stock up on the gin.</i>

612
00:55:50,093 --> 00:55:52,118
Boy drinks like a sailor.

613
00:55:56,266 --> 00:55:57,563
The Judge.

614
00:56:01,071 --> 00:56:02,333
Get out.

615
00:56:04,408 --> 00:56:05,670
Get out!

616
00:56:22,058 --> 00:56:23,548
Mr. Todd?

617
00:56:24,594 --> 00:56:26,221
At your service.

618
00:56:27,397 --> 00:56:30,525
<i>An honor to receive
your patronage, my lord.</i>

619
00:56:31,802 --> 00:56:33,497
<i>You know me, sir?</i>

620
00:56:33,904 --> 00:56:39,137
Who in this wide world
does not know the great Judge Turpin?

621
00:56:45,749 --> 00:56:47,649
<i>These premises
are hardly prepossessing,</i>

622
00:56:47,751 --> 00:56:49,582
and yet the Beadle tells me

623
00:56:49,686 --> 00:56:53,588
you're the most accomplished
of all the barbers in the city.

624
00:56:54,257 --> 00:56:56,623
<i>That is gracious of him, sir.</i>

625
00:56:57,694 --> 00:57:00,128
<i>What may I do for you today, sir?</i>

626
00:57:00,897 --> 00:57:03,695
A stylish trimming of the hair?

627
00:57:03,800 --> 00:57:05,791
Soothing skin massage?

628
00:57:05,902 --> 00:57:07,631
<i>Sit, sir. Sit.</i>

629
00:57:08,805 --> 00:57:13,765
<i>You see, sir, a man infatuate with love
Her ardent and eager slave</i>

630
00:57:13,877 --> 00:57:18,780
<i>So fetch the pomade and pumice stone
And lend me a more seductive tone</i>

631
00:57:18,882 --> 00:57:23,319
<i>A sprinkling perhaps of French cologne
But first, sir, I think</i>

632
00:57:24,387 --> 00:57:26,981
<i>a shave</i>

633
00:57:28,758 --> 00:57:31,852
<i>The closest I ever gave</i>

634
00:57:36,500 --> 00:57:38,798
<i>You're in a merry mood today, Mr. Todd.</i>

635
00:57:38,902 --> 00:57:44,067
<i>'Tis your delight, sir, catching fire
From one man to the next</i>

636
00:57:44,174 --> 00:57:46,734
<i>'Tis true, sir, love can still inspire</i>

637
00:57:46,843 --> 00:57:49,243
<i>The blood to pound
the heart leap higher</i>

638
00:57:49,346 --> 00:57:50,711
<i>- What more
- What more</i>

639
00:57:50,814 --> 00:57:52,975
<i>- can man require than love, sir
- can man require</i>

640
00:57:53,083 --> 00:57:54,277
<i>More than love, sir</i>

641
00:57:54,384 --> 00:57:55,681
<i>- What, sir?
- Women</i>

642
00:57:55,785 --> 00:57:58,219
<i>- Yes, women
- Pretty women</i>

643
00:58:29,419 --> 00:58:33,583
<i>Now then, my friend</i>

644
00:58:34,691 --> 00:58:38,559
<i>Now to your purpose</i>

645
00:58:39,563 --> 00:58:43,294
<i>Patience, enjoy it</i>

646
00:58:44,167 --> 00:58:48,604
<i>Revenge can't be taken in haste</i>

647
00:58:48,705 --> 00:58:50,900
<i>Make haste, and if we wed
You'll be commended, sir</i>

648
00:58:51,007 --> 00:58:52,372
<i>My lord</i>

649
00:58:54,978 --> 00:58:57,412
<i>And who, may it be said
Is your intended, sir?</i>

650
00:58:57,514 --> 00:59:00,005
<i>My ward</i>

651
00:59:01,251 --> 00:59:03,583
A pretty little rosebud.

652
00:59:03,687 --> 00:59:05,587
Pretty as her mother?

653
00:59:06,623 --> 00:59:09,217
What? What was that?

654
00:59:09,326 --> 00:59:13,626
<i>Nothing, sir. Nothing. May we proceed?</i>

655
00:59:15,365 --> 00:59:16,957
<i>Pretty women</i>

656
00:59:17,567 --> 00:59:21,936
<i>Fascinating
Sipping coffee</i>

657
00:59:22,806 --> 00:59:27,937
<i>Dancing
Pretty women!</i>

658
00:59:28,044 --> 00:59:30,410
<i>Are a wonder</i>

659
00:59:30,513 --> 00:59:32,981
<i>Pretty women</i>

660
00:59:35,785 --> 00:59:40,654
<i>Sitting in the window or</i>

661
00:59:40,757 --> 00:59:45,660
<i>Standing on the stair</i>

662
00:59:45,762 --> 00:59:52,361
<i>Something in them
Cheers the air</i>

663
00:59:56,039 --> 00:59:57,836
<i>Pretty women</i>

664
00:59:58,842 --> 01:00:00,673
<i>Silhouetted</i>

665
01:00:01,311 --> 01:00:03,711
<i>Stay within you</i>

666
01:00:03,813 --> 01:00:06,338
<i>Glancing!</i>

667
01:00:06,449 --> 01:00:08,713
<i>Stay forever</i>

668
01:00:08,818 --> 01:00:11,446
<i>Breathing lightly</i>

669
01:00:11,554 --> 01:00:13,647
<i>Pretty women</i>

670
01:00:13,757 --> 01:00:16,157
<i>- Pretty women
- Pretty women</i>

671
01:00:16,259 --> 01:00:21,026
<i>- Blowing out their candles or
- Blowing out their candles or</i>

672
01:00:21,131 --> 01:00:24,396
<i>- Combing out their hair
- Combing out their hair</i>

673
01:00:24,501 --> 01:00:26,025
<i>Then they leave</i>

674
01:00:26,136 --> 01:00:28,036
<i>- Even when they leave...
- Even when they</i>

675
01:00:28,138 --> 01:00:29,662
<i>leave you and vanish...</i>

676
01:00:29,773 --> 01:00:32,674
<i>- ... they still...
- ... they somehow can still remain...</i>

677
01:00:32,776 --> 01:00:38,237
<i>- ... are there, they're there
