<i>And in that darkness when I'm blind
With what I can't forget</i>

900
01:16:30,761 --> 01:16:31,785
<i>Johanna</i>

901
01:16:31,896 --> 01:16:34,922
<i>It's always morning in my mind</i>

902
01:16:35,032 --> 01:16:41,301
<i>My little lamb, my pet, Johanna</i>

903
01:16:44,308 --> 01:16:47,471
<i>- You stay, Johanna...
- Johanna</i>

904
01:16:47,578 --> 01:16:50,308
<i>...the way I've dreamed you are</i>

905
01:16:50,815 --> 01:16:54,410
<i>Oh, look, Johanna! A star!</i>

906
01:16:54,518 --> 01:16:59,080
<i>Buried sweetly in your yellow hair</i>

907
01:16:59,190 --> 01:17:02,591
<i>A shooting star!</i>

908
01:17:06,497 --> 01:17:10,433
<i>There, there, somebody, somebody
look up there. Didn't I tell you?</i>

909
01:17:10,534 --> 01:17:14,436
<i>Smell that air. City on fire!</i>

910
01:17:14,538 --> 01:17:17,439
<i>Quick, sir, run and tell
Warn them all of the witch's spell</i>

911
01:17:17,541 --> 01:17:19,168
<i>There it is, there it is, the unholy smell</i>

912
01:17:19,276 --> 01:17:21,471
<i>Tell it to the Beadle and police as well
Tell them! Tell them</i>

913
01:17:21,579 --> 01:17:25,413
<i>Help, fiend! City on fire!</i>

914
01:17:25,516 --> 01:17:28,917
<i>City on fire</i>

915
01:17:29,020 --> 01:17:30,783
Mischief. Mischief.

916
01:17:40,631 --> 01:17:47,059
<i>And though I'll think of you, I guess
Until the day I die</i>

917
01:17:47,171 --> 01:17:52,871
<i>I think I miss you less and less
As every day goes by</i>

918
01:17:52,977 --> 01:17:59,712
<i>- Johanna
- Johanna</i>

919
01:17:59,817 --> 01:18:06,154
<i>And you'd be beautiful and pale
And look too much like her</i>

920
01:18:06,257 --> 01:18:11,957
<i>If only angels could prevail
We'd be the way we were</i>

921
01:18:12,063 --> 01:18:18,935
<i>- Johanna
- I feel you, Johanna</i>

922
01:18:19,036 --> 01:18:22,062
<i>Wake up, Johanna</i>

923
01:18:22,173 --> 01:18:25,267
<i>Another bright red day</i>

924
01:18:25,376 --> 01:18:32,077
<i>We learn, Johanna, to say</i>

925
01:18:33,751 --> 01:18:35,241
<i>Goodbye</i>

926
01:18:38,923 --> 01:18:42,484
<i>I'll steal</i>

927
01:18:45,563 --> 01:18:50,432
<i>you</i>

928
01:19:27,905 --> 01:19:31,671
<i>Ladies and gentlemen
May I have your attention, please?</i>

929
01:19:33,244 --> 01:19:35,235
<i>Are your nostrils a-quiver
and tingling as well</i>

930
01:19:35,346 --> 01:19:38,406
<i>At that delicate
luscious ambrosial smell?</i>

931
01:19:38,516 --> 01:19:40,609
<i>Yes, they are, I can tell</i>

932
01:19:40,718 --> 01:19:44,552
<i>Well, ladies and gentlemen
That aroma enriching the breeze</i>

933
01:19:44,655 --> 01:19:46,589
<i>Is like nothing
compared to its succulent source</i>

934
01:19:46,690 --> 01:19:50,353
<i>As the gourmets among you
will tell you, of course</i>

935
01:19:50,461 --> 01:19:55,296
<i>Ladies and gentlemen
You can't imagine the rapture in store</i>

936
01:19:56,333 --> 01:19:58,631
<i>Just inside of this door!</i>

937
01:20:02,907 --> 01:20:06,365
<i>There you'll sample
Mrs. Lovett's meat pies</i>

938
01:20:06,477 --> 01:20:09,935
<i>Savory and sweet pies
As you'll see</i>

939
01:20:10,047 --> 01:20:13,505
<i>You who eat pies
Mrs. Lovett's meat pies</i>

940
01:20:13,617 --> 01:20:17,109
<i>Conjure up the treat
pies used to be!</i>

941
01:20:20,858 --> 01:20:22,587
<i>- Toby!
- Coming!</i>

942
01:20:23,661 --> 01:20:25,390
<i>- Ale there!
- Right, ma'am!</i>

943
01:20:25,496 --> 01:20:26,895
<i>Quick, now!</i>

944
01:20:28,132 --> 01:20:31,761
<i>Nice to see you, dearie
How have you been keeping?</i>

945
01:20:31,869 --> 01:20:35,464
<i>Cor, me bones is weary
Toby! One for the gentleman</i>

946
01:20:35,573 --> 01:20:39,134
<i>Hear the birdies cheeping
Helps to keep it cheery</i>

947
01:20:39,243 --> 01:20:42,679
<i>Toby! Throw the old woman out!</i>

948
01:20:42,780 --> 01:20:46,580
<i>What's my secret?
Frankly, dear, forgive my candor</i>

949
01:20:46,684 --> 01:20:50,142
<i>Family secret
All to do with herbs</i>

950
01:20:50,254 --> 01:20:53,712
<i>Things like being
careful with your coriander</i>

951
01:20:53,824 --> 01:20:56,555
<i>That's what makes the gravy grander!</i>

952
01:21:06,403 --> 01:21:09,930
<i>Eat them slow and feel the crust
How thin she rolled it</i>

953
01:21:10,040 --> 01:21:13,669
<i>Eat them slow
'cause every one's a prize!</i>

954
01:21:13,777 --> 01:21:17,213
<i>Eat them slow 'cause that's the lot
and now we've sold it!</i>

955
01:21:17,314 --> 01:21:18,576
<i>Come again tomorrow!</i>

956
01:21:18,682 --> 01:21:19,979
<i>Hold it!</i>

957
01:21:20,985 --> 01:21:23,044
<i>Bless my eyes!</i>

958
01:21:24,688 --> 01:21:26,622
<i>Fresh supplies!</i>

959
01:21:26,724 --> 01:21:28,089
<i>- How about it, dearie?
- Is that a pie...</i>

960
01:21:28,192 --> 01:21:29,989
<i>- Be here in a twinkling!
- ... fit for a king</i>

961
01:21:30,094 --> 01:21:32,722
<i>- Just confirms me theory, Toby!
- A wondrous sweet</i>

962
01:21:32,830 --> 01:21:33,990
<i>- and most delectable thing?
- God watches over us</i>

963
01:21:34,098 --> 01:21:35,793
<i>Didn't have an inkling, positively eerie</i>

964
01:21:35,899 --> 01:21:37,196
<i>You see, ma'am
why there's no meat pie</i>

965
01:21:37,301 --> 01:21:39,963
Toby! Throw the old woman out!

966
01:21:48,045 --> 01:21:51,310
Still got to keep an eye
on the household expenditure.

967
01:21:52,950 --> 01:21:55,578
<i>Which isn't to say we couldn't get
some nice taxidermy animals,</i>

968
01:21:55,686 --> 01:21:57,984
bring a touch of gentility to the place.

969
01:21:58,088 --> 01:22:00,579
<i>You know, a boar's head or two?</i>

970
01:22:01,792 --> 01:22:05,558
- Mr. T? You listening to me?
- Of course.

971
01:22:06,163 --> 01:22:11,226
- Then what did I just say?
- There must be a way to the Judge.

972
01:22:11,335 --> 01:22:14,463
Judge. Always harping
on the bloody old judge.

973
01:22:15,506 --> 01:22:17,736
We got a nice
respectable business now.

974
01:22:17,841 --> 01:22:19,706
Money coming in regular-like.

975
01:22:19,810 --> 01:22:21,505
<i>And since we're careful
to pick and choose,</i>

976
01:22:21,612 --> 01:22:25,776
<i>strangers, people who won't be missed,
who's gonna catch on?</i>

977
01:22:27,418 --> 01:22:29,545
<i>Mr. Todd, I'm so happy</i>

978
01:22:29,653 --> 01:22:31,780
<i>I could eat you up, I really could</i>

979
01:22:31,889 --> 01:22:35,120
<i>You know what I'd like to do, Mr. Todd?
What I dream?</i>

980
01:22:35,225 --> 01:22:38,922
<i>If the business stays as good
Where I'd really like to go</i>

981
01:22:39,530 --> 01:22:43,864
<i>In a year or so?
Don't you want to know?</i>

982
01:22:43,967 --> 01:22:45,093
Of course.

983
01:22:45,202 --> 01:22:47,033
<i>Do you really want to know?</i>

984
01:22:47,137 --> 01:22:49,037
<i>Yes, I do.</i>

985
01:23:03,787 --> 01:23:06,756
<i>By the sea, Mr. Todd
That's the life I'll covet</i>

986
01:23:06,857 --> 01:23:09,724
<i>By the sea, Mr. Todd
Oh, I know you'd love it</i>

987
01:23:09,827 --> 01:23:14,855
<i>You and me, Mr. T, we could be alone
In a house what we'd almost own</i>

988
01:23:14,965 --> 01:23:18,196
<i>- Down by the sea
- Anything you say</i>

989
01:23:18,302 --> 01:23:21,100
<i>Wouldn't that be smashing?</i>

990
01:23:22,005 --> 01:23:25,133
<i>Think how snug it'll be
Underneath our flannel</i>

991
01:23:25,242 --> 01:23:28,211
<i>When it's just you and me
And the English Channel</i>

992
01:23:28,312 --> 01:23:31,110
<i>In our cozy retreat
Kept all neat and tidy</i>

993
01:23:31,215 --> 01:23:36,380
<i>We'll have chums over every Friday
By the sea</i>

994
01:23:36,487 --> 01:23:41,982
<i>Don't you love the weather
by the sea?</i>

995
01:23:42,860 --> 01:23:45,954
<i>We'll grow old together</i>

996
01:23:46,263 --> 01:23:50,723
<i>By the seaside
By the beautiful sea</i>

997
01:23:55,839 --> 01:23:58,831
<i>It'll be so quiet that who'll come by it</i>

998
01:23:58,942 --> 01:24:01,274
<i>except a seagull?</i>

999
01:24:02,146 --> 01:24:06,583
<i>We shouldn't try it
though, till it's legal for two!</i>

1000
01:24:07,951 --> 01:24:11,079
<i>But a seaside wedding could be devised</i>

1001
01:24:11,188 --> 01:24:14,021
<i>Me rumpled bedding legitimized</i>

1002
01:24:14,124 --> 01:24:19,756
<i>Me eyelids'll flutter, I'll turn into butter
The moment I mutter "I do!"</i>

1003
01:24:19,863 --> 01:24:23,526
Will you take this woman
to be your lawfully wedded wife?

1004
01:24:27,671 --> 01:24:29,696
You may kiss your bride.

1005
01:24:42,085 --> 01:24:47,955
<i>Down by the sea
Married nice and proper</i>

1006
01:24:48,158 --> 01:24:53,755
<i>By the sea
Bring along your chopper</i>

1007
01:24:53,864 --> 01:25:00,326
<i>To the seaside
By the beautiful sea</i>

1008
01:25:18,555 --> 01:25:21,183
<i>I brought you some breakfast, dear.</i>

1009
01:25:25,062 --> 01:25:28,088
Mr. T? Can I ask you a question?

1010
01:25:29,299 --> 01:25:30,391
What?

1011
01:25:31,468 --> 01:25:33,766
What did your Lucy look like?

1012
01:25:36,707 --> 01:25:38,971
<i>Can't really remember, can you?</i>

1013
01:25:40,310 --> 01:25:42,278
She had yellow hair.

1014
01:25:44,214 --> 01:25:47,115
<i>You gotta leave this all behind,
you know.</i>

1015
01:25:48,919 --> 01:25:50,511
She's gone.

1016
01:25:52,155 --> 01:25:54,453
<i>Life is for the alive, my dear.</i>

1017
01:25:55,592 --> 01:25:58,322
<i>We could have a life, us two.</i>

1018
01:25:58,428 --> 01:26:00,453
Maybe not like I dreamed.

1019
01:26:01,532 --> 01:26:03,693
Maybe not like you remember.

1020
01:26:04,768 --> 01:26:06,565
But we could get by.

1021
01:26:15,178 --> 01:26:19,308
<i>- Mr. Todd! Mrs. Lovett, ma'am?
- What is it, Anthony?</i>

1022
01:26:19,416 --> 01:26:23,284
- He has her locked in a madhouse.
- Johanna.

1023
01:26:23,387 --> 01:26:24,854
Fogg's Asylum.

1024
01:26:24,955 --> 01:26:29,722
I've circled the place a dozen times.
There's no way in. It's a fortress.

1025
01:26:29,826 --> 01:26:32,727
- I've got him.
- Mr. Todd?

1026
01:26:33,997 --> 01:26:35,624
We've got her.

1027
01:26:36,967 --> 01:26:38,332
Where do you suppose
all the wigmakers

1028
01:26:38,435 --> 01:26:40,869
in London go to obtain their hair?

1029
01:26:41,672 --> 01:26:42,900
Bedlam.

1030
01:26:43,707 --> 01:26:47,575
- They get it from the lunatics at Bedlam.
- I don't understand.

1031
01:26:49,079 --> 01:26:52,105
We shall set you up
as a wigmaker's apprentice.

1032
01:26:52,215 --> 01:26:55,343
That'll gain you access.
And then you take her.

1033
01:26:56,086 --> 01:26:57,747
<i>Go, quickly, go!</i>

1034
01:26:59,256 --> 01:27:00,689
Fetch the boy.

1035
01:27:00,791 --> 01:27:04,124
Don't you think you should
leave the boy behind?

1036
01:27:18,675 --> 01:27:22,771
<i>- Toby. Mr. Todd needs you.
- Yes, ma'am.</i>

1037
01:27:35,759 --> 01:27:37,090
Mr. T?

1038
01:27:39,663 --> 01:27:43,622
<i>- Do you know where the Old Bailey is?
- Yes, sir. Not that I ever been there.</i>

1039
01:27:43,734 --> 01:27:47,830
Take this there.
Seek out a Judge Turpin. Repeat that.

1040
01:27:47,938 --> 01:27:50,406
Go to Old Bailey. Find Judge Turpin.

1041
01:27:50,507 --> 01:27:53,943
<i>You put that into his hands.
Only to him, you understand?</i>

1042
01:27:54,044 --> 01:27:55,136
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

1043
01:27:55,245 --> 01:27:57,509
<i>And while I'm out, do you mind
if I stop by the grocer just to pick...</i>

1044
01:27:57,614 --> 01:28:00,276
<i>No. You're not to stop,
you're not to speak.</i>

1045
01:28:00,384 --> 01:28:02,978
You're to deliver the letter.
Do you understand?

1046
01:28:03,086 --> 01:28:04,610
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

1047
01:28:34,785 --> 01:28:36,252
<i>Where you been, lad?</i>

1048
01:28:36,353 --> 01:28:41,017
We had quite the rush at dinner time.
Me poor bones is ready to drop.

1049
01:28:41,124 --> 01:28:43,422
Mr. Todd sent me on an errand.

1050
01:28:43,527 --> 01:28:44,516
<i>And on the way back,</i>

1051
01:28:44,628 --> 01:28:47,495
<i>I went by the workhouse,
just to take a look.</i>

1052
01:28:47,597 --> 01:28:51,397
<i>And I was thinking, but for you,
I'd be there now.</i>

1053
01:28:52,502 --> 01:28:54,299
Or someplace worse.

1054
01:28:54,404 --> 01:28:56,395
Seems like the good Lord
sent you for me.

1055
01:28:56,506 --> 01:28:59,873
<i>Oh, love, I feel quite the same way.</i>

1056
01:28:59,976 --> 01:29:01,876
<i>Listen to me, please.</i>

1057
01:29:01,978 --> 01:29:04,242
You know there's nothing
I wouldn't do for you.

1058
01:29:04,347 --> 01:29:07,475
<i>Say, if there were someone around,</i>

1059
01:29:08,385 --> 01:29:10,148
someone bad?

1060
01:29:10,754 --> 01:29:13,154
Only you didn't know it.

1061
01:29:13,256 --> 01:29:16,987
What is this?
What are you talking about?

1062
01:29:19,129 --> 01:29:25,591
<i>Nothing's gonna harm you
Not while I'm around</i>

1063
01:29:27,070 --> 01:29:32,565
<i>Nothing's gonna harm you
No, sir, not while I'm around</i>

1064
01:29:32,676 --> 01:29:34,200
What do you mean "someone bad"?

1065
01:29:34,311 --> 01:29:40,841
<i>Demons are prowling everywhere
nowadays</i>

1066
01:29:41,685 --> 01:29:47,954
<i>I'll send them howling, I don't care
I got ways</i>

1067
01:29:49,226 --> 01:29:52,161
<i>Hush, darling, there's no need for this.</i>

1068
01:29:53,897 --> 01:30:00,268
<i>No one's gonna hurt you
No one's gonna dare</i>

1069
01:30:01,538 --> 01:30:07,170
<i>Others can desert you
Not to worry, whistle, I'll be there</i>

1070
01:30:08,011 --> 01:30:11,777
<i>Demons will charm you
With a smile</i>

1071
01:30:11,882 --> 01:30:17,684
<i>For a while, but in time</i>

1072
01:30:17,788 --> 01:30:20,552
<i>Nothing can harm you</i>

1073
01:30:21,792 --> 01:30:26,923
<i>Not while I'm around</i>

1074
01:30:30,534 --> 01:30:32,195
<i>That's nice, dear.</i>

1075
01:30:32,903 --> 01:30:37,533
<i>Now, what is all this foolishness?
What are you talking about?</i>

1076
01:30:38,275 --> 01:30:42,143
Little things that
I've been thinking about Mr. Todd.

1077
01:30:43,113 --> 01:30:48,107
<i>Not to worry, not to worry
I may not be smart, but I ain't dumb</i>

1078
01:30:49,386 --> 01:30:54,585
<i>I can do it, put me to it
Show me something I can overcome</i>

1079
01:30:55,859 --> 01:30:59,886
<i>Not to worry, ma'am</i>

1080
01:31:02,699 --> 01:31:07,193
<i>Being close and being clever
Ain't like being true</i>

1081
01:31:08,271 --> 01:31:13,800
<i>I don't need to, I won't never
Hide a thing from you</i>

1082
01:31:13,910 --> 01:31:17,311
<i>Like some</i>

1083
01:31:19,082 --> 01:31:23,280
<i>Now, Toby, dear, haven't we
had enough of this foolish chatter?</i>

1084
01:31:23,386 --> 01:31:24,717
Here.

1085
01:31:24,821 --> 01:31:29,986
How about I give you
a nice shiny new penny

1086
01:31:30,093 --> 01:31:32,823
and you go get us some toffees?

1087
01:31:35,165 --> 01:31:36,826
That's Signor Pirelli's purse!

1088
01:31:36,933 --> 01:31:39,766
<i>No, it's not. Just something Mr. T
gave me for my birthday.</i>

1089
01:31:39,870 --> 01:31:41,770
<i>That proves it! We gotta go, ma'am.</i>

1090
01:31:41,872 --> 01:31:43,999
We gotta find the Beadle
and get the law here!

1091
01:31:44,140 --> 01:31:46,973
<i>Toby. Hush, lad,
you're not going anywhere.</i>

1092
01:31:47,077 --> 01:31:52,071
<i>You just sit here, nice and quiet,
next to me. That's right, right.</i>

1093
01:31:54,985 --> 01:31:57,647
How could you think
such a thing of Mr. Todd?

1094
01:31:57,754 --> 01:32:00,279
He's been so good to us.

1095
01:32:04,494 --> 01:32:11,024
<i>Nothing's gonna harm you
Not while I'm around</i>

1096
01:32:12,836 --> 01:32:18,331
<i>Nothing's gonna harm you, darling
Not while I'm around</i>

1097
01:32:19,609 --> 01:32:25,275
<i>Demons'll charm you with a smile
For a while</i>

1098
01:32:25,382 --> 01:32:28,510
<i>But in time</i>

1099
01:32:28,618 --> 01:32:32,611
<i>Nothing's gonna harm you</i>

1100
01:32:32,722 --> 01:32:38,354
<i>Not while I'm around</i>

1101
01:32:42,132 --> 01:32:45,101
Funny we should be having
this little chat right now.

1102
01:32:45,201 --> 01:32:47,396
'Cause I was just thinking...

1103
01:32:48,305 --> 01:32:50,933
You know how you've always fancied
coming into the bake house with me

1104
01:32:51,041 --> 01:32:54,169
<i>- to help make the pies?
- Yes, ma'am.</i>

1105
01:32:54,344 --> 01:32:58,678
<i>Well, no time like the present, eh?</i>

1106
01:33:18,568 --> 01:33:22,004
<i>I feel bad for you, going up
and down all these stairs.</i>

1107
01:33:22,105 --> 01:33:25,905
<i>- Well, that'll be your job now.
- Yes, ma'am.</i>

1108
01:33:30,347 --> 01:33:32,611
<i>Quite a stink, ain't there?</i>

1109
01:33:36,319 --> 01:33:37,650
You see those grates?

1110
01:33:37,754 --> 01:33:40,552
<i>They go right down to the sewers,
and the smells come up.</i>

1111
01:33:40,657 --> 01:33:43,057
Always a few rats gone home
to Jesus down there.

1112
01:33:43,159 --> 01:33:47,061
<i>Now, this'll be the bake oven.
Three dozen at a time.</i>

1113
01:33:47,163 --> 01:33:49,927
<i>Always be sure
the door is closed properly, like this.</i>

1114
01:33:50,033 --> 01:33:53,628
- Door's closed properly.
