1115
01:33:54,237 --> 01:33:57,570
Pop in the meat. Give it a good grind.

1116
01:34:00,877 --> 01:34:02,572
Pops out there.

1117
01:34:04,481 --> 01:34:05,846
You try.

1118
01:34:07,550 --> 01:34:08,778
Good grind.

1119
01:34:10,420 --> 01:34:12,149
Comes out there.

1120
01:34:14,157 --> 01:34:15,488
That's my boy.

1121
01:34:15,592 --> 01:34:18,425
<i>I'm just gonna pop upstairs,
back in two shakes, all right?</i>

1122
01:34:18,528 --> 01:34:21,759
You mind if I have a pie while I wait?

1123
01:34:21,865 --> 01:34:23,856
<i>As many as you like, son.</i>

1124
01:34:36,679 --> 01:34:38,044
<i>Yes, sir, I agree.</i>

1125
01:34:38,148 --> 01:34:39,615
It would be to our mutual interest

1126
01:34:39,716 --> 01:34:43,652
to come to some arrangement
in regard to my poor children's hair.

1127
01:34:43,753 --> 01:34:45,186
Brunettes.

1128
01:34:46,756 --> 01:34:48,246
Redheads.

1129
01:34:50,960 --> 01:34:53,428
I keep the blondes in here.

1130
01:34:53,530 --> 01:34:56,090
<i>It was yellow hair
you was looking for, sir?</i>

1131
01:34:56,199 --> 01:34:57,564
Yes.

1132
01:35:28,631 --> 01:35:32,658
<i>- That one there has the shade I need.
- Come, child.</i>

1133
01:35:39,409 --> 01:35:42,901
Smile for the gentleman
and you shall have a sweetie.

1134
01:35:44,914 --> 01:35:47,178
<i>Now, where shall I cut?</i>

1135
01:35:48,585 --> 01:35:51,952
<i>Not another word, Mr. Fogg,
or it will be your last.</i>

1136
01:35:53,890 --> 01:35:58,759
<i>Now, I leave you
to the mercy of your children.</i>

1137
01:36:09,172 --> 01:36:12,505
<i>I got him locked in.
But if he escapes, he'll go to the law.</i>

1138
01:36:12,609 --> 01:36:14,839
<i>- Then he won't escape.
- I don't know, Mr. Todd.</i>

1139
01:36:14,944 --> 01:36:17,208
The Judge'll be here soon.

1140
01:36:18,781 --> 01:36:21,614
<i>'Scuse me, sir. Gave me a fright.</i>

1141
01:36:21,718 --> 01:36:24,710
<i>Not my intention, good madam.
I assure you.</i>

1142
01:36:25,488 --> 01:36:28,480
Though I am here on official business.

1143
01:36:29,159 --> 01:36:34,426
<i>You see, there's been some complaints
about the stink from your chimney.</i>

1144
01:36:34,531 --> 01:36:37,557
They say at night
it is something most foul.

1145
01:36:38,434 --> 01:36:41,528
Health regulations
and the general public welfare

1146
01:36:41,638 --> 01:36:43,538
<i>naturally being my duty,</i>

1147
01:36:43,640 --> 01:36:46,768
I'm afraid I'm gonna have to take a look

1148
01:36:49,646 --> 01:36:51,341
at your bakehouse.

1149
01:36:52,749 --> 01:36:54,239
<i>Of course, sir.</i>

1150
01:36:54,350 --> 01:36:58,013
<i>But first, why don't you come upstairs?
Let me pamper you.</i>

1151
01:36:59,789 --> 01:37:02,724
Much as I do appreciate
tonsorial doormen

1152
01:37:02,825 --> 01:37:05,293
I really ought to see
to my official obligations first.

1153
01:37:05,395 --> 01:37:07,386
I completely understand.

1154
01:37:10,767 --> 01:37:15,329
<i>If you'll indulge me, sir,
what is that exotic aroma?</i>

1155
01:37:18,308 --> 01:37:21,334
<i>Me secret, is a touch of ambergris.</i>

1156
01:37:22,712 --> 01:37:25,374
Dare I offer you something
a tad more appropriate

1157
01:37:25,481 --> 01:37:27,881
for a gentleman of your standing?

1158
01:37:27,984 --> 01:37:30,919
<i>The ladies will greatly appreciate it, sir.</i>

1159
01:37:33,790 --> 01:37:37,055
You're the expert in these matters.

1160
01:37:37,160 --> 01:37:39,094
Only take a moment.

1161
01:37:43,233 --> 01:37:45,724
<i>Would you like a bit of bay rum, sir?</i>

1162
01:37:45,835 --> 01:37:48,099
Bay rum is very bracing.

1163
01:38:53,936 --> 01:38:57,565
<i>Let me out! Please, let me out!</i>

1164
01:39:00,343 --> 01:39:01,970
Let me out!

1165
01:39:19,629 --> 01:39:20,789
Toby?

1166
01:39:22,598 --> 01:39:24,156
Where is he?

1167
01:39:28,271 --> 01:39:33,140
<i>Toby, where are you, love?</i>

1168
01:39:35,244 --> 01:39:36,506
Toby?

1169
01:39:40,483 --> 01:39:44,112
<i>Nothing's gonna harm you</i>

1170
01:39:44,220 --> 01:39:47,451
<i>Not while I'm around</i>

1171
01:39:47,557 --> 01:39:48,819
Toby?

1172
01:39:50,660 --> 01:39:52,924
<i>Where are you hiding?</i>

1173
01:39:54,464 --> 01:39:55,624
Toby?

1174
01:39:56,833 --> 01:40:00,030
<i>Nothing's gonna harm you, darling</i>

1175
01:40:02,538 --> 01:40:05,132
<i>Not while I'm around</i>

1176
01:40:09,178 --> 01:40:10,440
Toby?

1177
01:40:12,582 --> 01:40:14,015
Mr. Todd!

1178
01:40:16,052 --> 01:40:17,644
You wait for him here.

1179
01:40:17,754 --> 01:40:21,246
I'll return with a coach
in less than half an hour.

1180
01:40:21,357 --> 01:40:25,817
Don't worry. No one'll recognize you.
You're safe now.

1181
01:40:26,829 --> 01:40:31,664
<i>Safe? So, we run away
and then all our dreams come true?</i>

1182
01:40:32,769 --> 01:40:34,430
I hope so.

1183
01:40:35,238 --> 01:40:38,435
I've never had dreams. Only nightmares.

1184
01:40:39,442 --> 01:40:40,841
<i>Johanna,</i>

1185
01:40:41,577 --> 01:40:45,035
when we're free of this place
all the ghosts will go away.

1186
01:40:45,148 --> 01:40:48,584
<i>No, Anthony. They never go away.</i>

1187
01:40:49,652 --> 01:40:53,383
I'll be right back to you.
Half an hour and we'll be free.

1188
01:41:28,825 --> 01:41:31,453
<i>Beadle! Beadle!</i>

1189
01:41:32,662 --> 01:41:37,429
<i>No good hiding, I saw you</i>

1190
01:41:37,533 --> 01:41:42,493
<i>Are you in there still, Beadle?
Beadle?</i>

1191
01:41:42,605 --> 01:41:45,403
<i>Beadle, dear Beadle?</i>

1192
01:41:47,543 --> 01:41:50,671
<i>Beadle deedle deedle
deedle deedle dumpling</i>

1193
01:41:50,780 --> 01:41:52,975
<i>Beadle dumpling...</i>

1194
01:41:59,989 --> 01:42:03,015
Who are you?
What are you doing here?

1195
01:42:05,261 --> 01:42:06,751
<i>Evil is here, sir.</i>

1196
01:42:06,863 --> 01:42:11,459
<i>The stink of evil, from below, from her!
Oh, she's the Devil's wife.</i>

1197
01:42:11,567 --> 01:42:15,560
<i>Beware her, sir.
She with no pity in her heart.</i>

1198
01:42:17,573 --> 01:42:20,440
<i>Don't I know you, mister?</i>

1199
01:42:20,543 --> 01:42:22,010
Mr. Todd?

1200
01:42:33,456 --> 01:42:34,980
Where is she?

1201
01:42:36,425 --> 01:42:39,019
<i>Below, Your Honor. With my neighbor.</i>

1202
01:42:40,029 --> 01:42:43,590
Thank heavens
the sailor did not molest her.

1203
01:42:43,699 --> 01:42:48,261
<i>Thank heavens, too,
she has seen the error of her ways.</i>

1204
01:42:49,138 --> 01:42:51,402
<i>- She has?
- Oh, yes.</i>

1205
01:42:52,275 --> 01:42:54,573
Your lesson was well-learned.

1206
01:42:54,677 --> 01:42:58,773
She speaks only of you.
Longing for forgiveness.

1207
01:43:00,583 --> 01:43:02,744
Then she shall have it.

1208
01:43:03,819 --> 01:43:07,186
<i>- She'll be here soon, you say?
- Yes.</i>

1209
01:43:07,790 --> 01:43:09,758
<i>Excellent, my friend.</i>

1210
01:43:11,761 --> 01:43:13,422
How about a shave?

1211
01:43:14,830 --> 01:43:16,764
<i>Sit, sir. Sit.</i>

1212
01:43:19,769 --> 01:43:25,799
<i>- Oh, pretty women
- Pretty women, yes</i>

1213
01:43:25,908 --> 01:43:28,968
<i>Johanna, Johanna</i>

1214
01:43:29,078 --> 01:43:32,673
<i>Pretty women
Pretty women are a wonder</i>

1215
01:43:32,782 --> 01:43:34,374
<i>Pretty women!</i>

1216
01:43:34,483 --> 01:43:37,384
<i>What we do for pretty women!</i>

1217
01:43:37,486 --> 01:43:41,149
<i>- Blowing out their candles
- Blowing out their candles</i>

1218
01:43:41,257 --> 01:43:44,852
<i>- Or combing out their hair
- Or combing out their hair</i>

1219
01:43:44,961 --> 01:43:46,656
<i>Then they leave</i>

1220
01:43:46,762 --> 01:43:50,323
<i>- Even when they leave
- Even when they leave you and vanish</i>

1221
01:43:50,433 --> 01:43:53,334
<i>- They still are there
- They somehow can still remain</i>

1222
01:43:53,436 --> 01:43:58,373
<i>- There with you, there
- They're there</i>

1223
01:43:59,175 --> 01:44:02,770
How seldom it is
one meets a fellow spirit.

1224
01:44:02,878 --> 01:44:07,116
<i>With fellow tastes in women, at least.</i>

1225
01:44:07,950 --> 01:44:09,417
What's that?

1226
01:44:10,319 --> 01:44:13,220
<i>The years, no doubt,
have changed me, sir.</i>

1227
01:44:13,322 --> 01:44:16,223
<i>But then, I suppose the face of a barber,</i>

1228
01:44:16,325 --> 01:44:20,386
<i>the face of a prisoner,
a dog, is not particularly memorable.</i>

1229
01:44:27,136 --> 01:44:29,570
Benjamin Barker.

1230
01:44:29,905 --> 01:44:32,738
Benjamin Barker!

1231
01:45:10,579 --> 01:45:14,037
<i>Rest now, my friend</i>

1232
01:45:16,185 --> 01:45:20,417
<i>Rest now forever</i>

1233
01:45:21,891 --> 01:45:27,158
<i>Sleep now the untroubled</i>

1234
01:45:27,263 --> 01:45:32,826
<i>Sleep of the angels</i>

1235
01:45:44,013 --> 01:45:46,106
<i>Come for a shave, have you, lad?</i>

1236
01:45:46,215 --> 01:45:47,807
<i>No, I...</i>

1237
01:45:51,687 --> 01:45:54,451
Everyone needs a good shave.

1238
01:46:01,664 --> 01:46:03,723
Forget my face.

1239
01:46:07,570 --> 01:46:10,801
<i>Die! God in heaven, die!</i>

1240
01:46:24,653 --> 01:46:26,143
You.

1241
01:46:35,097 --> 01:46:36,894
Why did you scream?

1242
01:46:36,999 --> 01:46:39,968
<i>He was clutching onto me dress,
but he's finished now.</i>

1243
01:46:40,069 --> 01:46:42,503
I'll take care of it. Open the door.

1244
01:46:42,605 --> 01:46:44,903
<i>Open the door, I said.</i>

1245
01:47:39,094 --> 01:47:41,756
"Don't I know you?" she said.

1246
01:47:51,507 --> 01:47:53,338
You knew she lived.

1247
01:47:55,311 --> 01:47:57,575
I was only thinking of you.

1248
01:48:01,183 --> 01:48:03,151
You lied to me.

1249
01:48:03,252 --> 01:48:06,813
<i>No, no, not lied at all
No, I never lied</i>

1250
01:48:06,922 --> 01:48:08,583
<i>- Lucy...
- Said she took a poison</i>

1251
01:48:08,691 --> 01:48:10,591
<i>she did, never said that she died</i>

1252
01:48:10,693 --> 01:48:12,888
<i>- I've come home again
- Poor thing, she lived</i>

1253
01:48:12,995 --> 01:48:14,257
<i>But it left her weak in the head</i>

1254
01:48:14,363 --> 01:48:16,831
<i>All she did for months
was just lie there in bed</i>

1255
01:48:16,932 --> 01:48:18,297
<i>Should've been in hospital</i>

1256
01:48:18,400 --> 01:48:21,130
<i>Wound up in Bedlam instead
Poor thing!</i>

1257
01:48:21,237 --> 01:48:23,467
<i>- Better you should think she was dead
- Oh, my God!</i>

1258
01:48:23,572 --> 01:48:26,439
<i>Yes, I lied 'cause I love you!</i>

1259
01:48:26,542 --> 01:48:29,272
<i>- I'd be twice the wife she was!
- Lucy...</i>

1260
01:48:29,378 --> 01:48:31,676
<i>- I love you!
- What have I done?</i>

1261
01:48:31,780 --> 01:48:34,977
<i>Could that thing have
cared for you like me?</i>

1262
01:48:35,084 --> 01:48:38,144
<i>Mrs. Lovett, you're a bloody wonder
Eminently practical</i>

1263
01:48:38,254 --> 01:48:41,018
<i>And yet appropriate as always
As you've said repeatedly</i>

1264
01:48:41,123 --> 01:48:42,784
<i>There's little point in dwelling
on the past</i>

1265
01:48:42,892 --> 01:48:43,859
<i>- Now, come here, my love...
- Do you mean it?</i>

1266
01:48:43,959 --> 01:48:45,187
<i>Everything I did, I swear, I thought</i>

1267
01:48:45,294 --> 01:48:46,522
<i>- was only for the best
